# Accessibility & SEO

## Semantic HTML

- Use correct elements: `<button>` for actions, `<a>`/`<Link>` for navigation, `<input>` for form fields. Never `<div onClick>`.
- One `<h1>` per page. Headings sequential: h1 → h2 → h3. Never skip levels.
- Landmarks: `<header>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<aside>`, `<footer>`.
- Every `<section>` has a heading (visually hidden with `sr-only` if needed).

## Document Structure

```html
<a href="#main-content" class="sr-only focus:not-sr-only">Skip to content</a>
<header><nav aria-label="Main navigation">...</nav></header>
<main id="main-content">
  <section aria-labelledby="hero-heading"><h1 id="hero-heading">...</h1></section>
</main>
<footer><nav aria-label="Footer navigation">...</nav></footer>
```

## Keyboard Navigation

- All interactive elements reachable via keyboard.
- Visible focus states: `focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-accent focus-visible:outline-none`.
- Modals/menus trap focus while open, restore on close.
- `Escape` closes overlays. `Enter`/`Space` activates buttons.

## ARIA

- `aria-label` on icon-only buttons and image links.
- `aria-expanded` on toggle buttons (hamburger, accordions).
- `aria-current="page"` on active nav links.
- `aria-live="polite"` for dynamic content (form errors, toasts).
- Never use ARIA when a native HTML element does the same job.

## Color & Contrast

- WCAG AA: **4.5:1** body text, **3:1** large text.
- Never convey info through color alone — pair with text, icons, or patterns.

## axe Testing

- `@axe-core/react` in dev mode — logs violations to console.
- `jest-axe` / `vitest-axe` in component tests.
- Zero `critical` or `serious` violations per component.
- Run axe browser extension or Lighthouse a11y audit before release.

## SEO — Meta Tags

Every route defines `head` via TanStack Router:
- `<title>` — unique per page: `Page Name | Company Name`
- `<meta name="description">` — 150–160 chars, includes location + service
- All meta content translated via i18n.

## SEO — Structured Data

Add `AutoRepair` JSON-LD schema with name, address, telephone, openingHours, url.

## Component Completion Checklist

1. Keyboard-only usable?
2. Visible focus indication?
3. Semantic HTML (correct elements, heading hierarchy)?
4. ARIA attributes correct and minimal?
5. Meets contrast requirements?
6. Makes sense to a screen reader?
7. Passes axe with zero critical/serious violations?
